<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Jubal on 06-03-2001 06:57 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">There are lots of ways to screw an uberguild within the rules if you are imaginative about it.

- Uberguilds do need others to port/rez/group with. Not having cooperation of others slows them down a lot and makes them less able to screw with others. You do not need them at all. They will rarely help you anyway as they are too busy with their own stuff to bother.

- You can mess up the plans of an uberguild while going about your business. I found this out while killing dorfs in thurg b when an uberguild moved in to kill the Dain. It was impossible for them to do so while we were there.

- Uberguilds can only be in so many places at once. Consequently they can only screw with one other raid at a time. If there's a dozen raids going on on a server then 11 of them will proceed normally no matter what the uberguild does.

- If stuff happens like the story above with the monk training a Trak raid, a petition and email from all the members of the Trak raid can get the monk banned for sure, and can possibly get others in that guild banned as well for participating via coordinated action. In some cases it can get the guild disbanded as well by the GMs especially if there is a pattern of doing so.

Things that are bad ideas:

- FD trains, hello bannsville
- KS attempts, you can just forget it you'll never win a power battle with an uberguild
- harrassment, not only do you risk your account but you probably spur on more antisocial behavior and feed egos with the attention

There is a particular uberguild on my server that... irks me. I regularly rez members of this guild on the way to carrying out my own business. If they had to bring over their own cleric everytime this would result in a huge inconvenience for them. They know it too which is why they have yet to screw with anyone else's raid.

Rather than the top two guilds I find it tends to be the ones almost at the top who are the least considerate of others' raids, they're so busy trying to take over the leaders that they'll step on anyone to get there.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
